<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17540227-61">
               <interp inst="t17540227-61" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17540227-61" type="year" value="1754"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17540227-61" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17540227"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17540227-61" type="date" value="17540227"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17540227-61-off313-c441" targOrder="Y" targets="t17540227-61-defend561 t17540227-61-off313 t17540227-61-verdict316"></join>
         
               <p>119. (L.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17540227-61-defend561" type="defendantName">
                     Charles 
                     Barker 
                  <interp inst="t17540227-61-defend561" type="surname" value="Barker"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17540227-61-defend561" type="given" value="Charles"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17540227-61-defend561" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17540227-61-off313" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17540227-61-off313" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17540227-61-off313" type="offenceSubcategory" value="housebreaking"></interp>
               that he, on the <rs id="t17540227-61-cd314" type="crimeDate">21st of December</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17540227-61-off313 t17540227-61-cd314"></join>, the dwelling-house of 
                     
                        <persName id="t17540227-61-victim563" type="victimName">
                           John 
                           Greenhow 
                        <interp inst="t17540227-61-victim563" type="surname" value="Greenhow"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17540227-61-victim563" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17540227-61-victim563" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17540227-61-off313 t17540227-61-victim563"></join>
                     </persName>
                      
                   did break and enter, and two 36 s. pieces, one moidore, and three guineas, the money of the said John, in the dwelling-house did steal
            </rs>, &amp;c. ++</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17540227-61-person564">
                  John 
                  Greenhow 
               <interp inst="t17540227-61-person564" type="surname" value="Greenhow"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17540227-61-person564" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17540227-61-person564" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live at the <placeName id="t17540227-61-crimeloc315">Castle Inn in Wood-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17540227-61-crimeloc315" type="placeName" value="Castle Inn in Wood-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17540227-61-crimeloc315" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17540227-61-off313 t17540227-61-crimeloc315"></join>, on the 22d of December, when I was called up in the morning, I found my counting-house, adjoining to my dwelling-house, broke open, and the money missing which is mentioned in the indictment; the prisoner had lived servant with me about nine or ten weeks, but I had discharged him, but let him lie in my house. He lay there the night this happened, and I took him up on suspicion; he confessed he had taken two 36 s. pieces, a moidore, and three guineas; and by his direction we found the two 36 s. pieces and moidore in an old frock in his box, which was in my house, he said he had made use of the three guineas.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17540227-61-person565">
                  Robert 
                  Paterson 
               <interp inst="t17540227-61-person565" type="surname" value="Paterson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17540227-61-person565" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17540227-61-person565" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , the constable, confirmed that of the prisoner's confession, and the finding the money.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17540227-61-verdict316" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17540227-61-verdict316" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17540227-61-verdict316" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder40s"></interp>
               Guilty 39 s.
            </rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17540227-61-punish317" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17540227-61-punish317" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17540227-61-defend561 t17540227-61-punish317"></join>
               
                     <note>[Transportation. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
